The paper discusses a framework for automatically generating assurance cases based on a system model specified in an architectural design language, logical rules expressed in a domain-specific language, and the results of other formal analyses. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a domain-specific language, which could indicate that it belongs to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of formal methods and logical foundations, which could suggest that it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the assurance of complex systems, which could indicate that it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
